'''Cannabis in Bahrain''' is illegal.

==Use==
A 2000 report by [[UNODC]] estimated the prevalence of adult use of cannabis in Bahrain to be between .1-.4%.<ref name="Hawdon2005">{{cite book|author=James Hawdon|title=Drug and Alcohol Consumption as Functions of Social Structures: A Cross-cultural Sociology|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=SpMbAQAAMAAJ|date=January 2005|publisher=Edwin Mellen Press|isbn=978-0-7734-6187-1|page=65}}</ref>

==Enforcement==
In 2014 a Bahraini citizen was arrested for growing cannabis plants at his house, and possessing 767 grams of hashish. He was convicted of possessing and growing cannabis, though not of trafficking it since no evidence of sale was found, and sentenced to 12 months in jail and fined BD1,000.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.tradearabia.com/news/MISC_259810.html |title=Marijuana plant grower jailed in Bahrain |publisher=Tradearabia.com |date=2014-06-10 |accessdate=2016-11-30}}</ref>

